  "narrative": "Grand River Health received $2.13 billion in provincial funding over 5 fiscal years (2020–2024), with only 2 named officers in CRA T3010 filings: CEO Ron Gagnon and CFO Doug Murray. Government funding accounts for 79–83% of total revenue each year. This extreme governance concentration — a $2.1B public institution with just 2 declared officers — represents one of the most striking patterns in the dataset. While likely a health authority with broader governance not captured in T3010 filings, the reporting gap itself warrants scrutiny."
